- cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper uses deep learning to infer 3D shapes from 2D sketches, which is a common application of computer vision. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses deep learning to learn priors for 3D shape inference, which falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses deep learning to infer 3D shapes from 2D sketches, which is a common application of machine learning. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry): The paper deals with inferring 3D shapes from 2D sketches, which involves computational geometry techniques such as surface parameterization and intersection detection.
